## Development setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/frusp/fffuuu
cd fffuuu
pip install -e .          # requires pip >= 22 + setuptools >= 68 + Python 3.11+

# test with an isolated data dir
FFF_DIR=/tmp/fff-test fffuuu init
FFF_DIR=/tmp/fff-test fck oncall
```

**Note:** The development machine this was built on runs Python 3.10 / pip 22
/ setuptools 59 (WSL). These are all below the project's requirements.
The code is correct — the environment is the issue. Use Python 3.11+ to
develop and test.

---

## Decisions made and why

| Decision | Reason |
|---|---|
| Package dir named `fffuuu/` (not `fff/`) | Consistency with PyPI name and repo name |
| Flat layout (not `src/`) | Simple CLI tool, no library consumers, no test suite yet |
| Three entry-point aliases | Different teams have different cultures; the tool should meet them where they are |
| `tomllib` (stdlib) instead of `tomli` | Avoids adding any dependency, even a dev one |
| No `click` / `typer` | Would be a runtime dependency; `argparse` is sufficient |
| `~/.fff/` data dir (not `~/.config/fffuuu/`) | Shorter to type under stress; SRE muscle memory |
| `FFF_DIR` env var | Enables isolated testing without mocking |

---

## Conventions

- All output goes through `display.py` — never `print()` directly in
  `commands.py` except for raw data output (`cmd_where`, `cmd_export`).
- Command functions are named `cmd_<subcommand>` and always return an `int`
  exit code (0 = success, 1 = error).
- `store.load_contacts()` returns `[]` when the file doesn't exist (not an
  error). Commands decide what to do with an empty list.
- No comments unless the why is non-obvious. No docstrings on `cmd_*`
  functions — the `--help` string is the documentation.

